<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1725" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1725">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.812/131.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Long</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">San Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 9, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s April 4. The President expressed gratification that our
                            Government was disposed to consider favorably his [omission in <pb facs="1234" n="1118" xml:id="pg_1118"/> transmission]. * * * While
                            discussing in some detail the school, he expressed the opinion that all
                            Central America should enjoy the privilege of entering its students
                            under certain rules and regulations.</p>
                        <p>He made clear, however, that his first and greatest desire was to see
                            Salvador put on a gold basis, and thought the matter could be arranged.
                            * * *</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Long.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>